From: Kuniyuki Iwashima <kuniyu@amazon.com>
Date: Tue, 4 Jun 2024 09:52:32 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] af_unix: Annotate data-race of sk->sk_state in unix_accept().
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 6.9.6
Git-commit: 1b536948e805aab61a48c5aa5db10c9afee880bd

[ Upstream commit 1b536948e805aab61a48c5aa5db10c9afee880bd ]

Once sk->sk_state is changed to TCP_LISTEN, it never changes.

unix_accept() takes the advantage and reads sk->sk_state without
holding unix_state_lock().

Let's use READ_ONCE() there.

Fixes: 1da177e4c3f4 ("Linux-2.6.12-rc2")
Signed-off-by: Kuniyuki Iwashima <kuniyu@amazon.com>
Signed-off-by: Paolo Abeni <pabeni@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Sasha Levin <sashal@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 net/unix/af_unix.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/net/unix/af_unix.c b/net/unix/af_unix.c
index cbc011ce..4647fb5e 100644
--- a/net/unix/af_unix.c
+++ b/net/unix/af_unix.c
@@ -1704,7 +1704,7 @@ static int unix_accept(struct socket *sock, struct socket *newsock, int flags,
 		goto out;
 
 	err = -EINVAL;
-	if (sk->sk_state != TCP_LISTEN)
+	if (READ_ONCE(sk->sk_state) != TCP_LISTEN)
 		goto out;
 
